eriRouterL2VpnMIB.name: eriRouterL2VpnMIB

revisions.description: Updated RBN/rbn/Rbn as ERICSSON-ROUTER/eriRouter/EriRouter to migrate RBN MIB to ERICSSON MIB.

The key changes made to this MIB module are as follows: (1) Added eriRouterUdpL2VpnStaticTable. (2) Added eriRouterUdpL2VpnStaticTable compliance information: eriRouterUdpL2VpnPwMIBCompliance, eriRouterUdpL2VpnStaticPwGroup. (3) Added EriRouterVpnPsnType. (4) Added encapError(23) in EriRouterVpnPwFlagsType. (5) Changed eriRouterMplsL2VpnMIBGroups and eriRouterMplsL2VpnMIBCompliances status to current.

This version is to support PW and PW state change notifications. The key changes made to this MIB module are as follows: (1) Updated ORGANIZATION/CONTACT-INFO (2) Obsolete all MIB objects under eriRouterL2VpnMIBObjects and eriRouterL2VpnMIBConformance. (3) Deprecated eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticXcFlags eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpXcCctUp, eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpXcFlags (4) Added EriRouterVpnPwFlagsType, and EriRouterVpnPwStateType TEXTUAL-CONVENTIONs. (5) Added new objects eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticPwFlags, eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticPwState, eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpPwFlags, eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpPwState to indicate L2VPN pseduowire flags and states. (6) Added eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpPwStateChange notification. (7) Added PW compliance and object groups: eriRouterMplsL2VpnPwMIBCompliance, eriRouterMplsL2VpnPwScalarGroup, eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticPwGroup, eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpPwGroup.

Updated EriRouterVpnXcFlagsType TC. (1) Deprecated ismUp(12) (2) Added primary(17), backup(18), primaryAutoRevert(19), standby(20), cwMismatch(21), sigParamsMatch(22) Updated the description of both eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpXcCctUp and eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpInputCctUp

This version is to redefine L2Vpn Static and LDP tables for indexing consistency with an MPLS L2VPN implementation on a device. The key changes made to this MIB module are as follows. (1) Deprecated all MIB objects under eriRouterL2VpnMIBObjects. (2) Added eriRouterMplsL2VpnMIBObjects. (3) Redefined objects corresponding to deprecated objects under eriRouterL2VpnMIBObjects. (4) Deprecated all MIB objects under eriRouterL2VpnMIBConformance (5) Added eriRouterMplsL2VpnMIBConformance. (6) Redefined objects corresponding to deprecated objects under eriRouterMplsL2VpnMIBConformance. (7) Changed VPN virtual circuit id (eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpVcId) SYNTAX to Unsigned32 (0..4294967295).

eriRouterMplsL2VpnNotificationEnable.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnNotificationEnable
eriRouterMplsL2VpnNotificationEnable.reference: See also [RFC3413] for explanation that notifications are under the ultimate control of the MIB modules in this document.
eriRouterMplsL2VpnNotificationEnable.description: If this object is true, then it enables the generation of all notifications defined in this MIB. This object's value should be preserved across agent reboots.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticTable.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticTable
eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticTable.description: This table contains objects which identify static Layer 2 VPN circuits. With respect to creation and deletion of entries in this table, rows are created or deleted when the VPN circuit is configured.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticTable.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticInLabel.description: This object indicates the value used by the remote connection in order to identify this VPN circuit when communicating with the label manager (Label allocated in the local node)

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticPeerAddr.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticPeerAddr
eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticPeerAddr.description: This object indicates the ip address of the VPN peer.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticCctHandle.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticCctHandle
eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticCctHandle.description: This object indicates the internal representation of the physical circuit to which this VPN is connected. A hexadecimal value of ff ff ff ff ff ff ff ff indicates an invalid circuit.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticInputCctUp.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticInputCctUp
eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticInputCctUp.description: This object indicates the status of the VPN attachment circuit. A value of true indicates that the VPN attachment circuit is connected with its remote site. A value of false indicates that the remote site is not presently connected.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticXcFlags.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticXcFlags
eriRouterMplsL2VpnStaticXcFlags.description: This object indicates more detailed information on the status of the VPN circuit. This object is a bit field so it may contain one or more of these values.

A value of down(2) indicates that the remote site is not presently connected. A value of standby(3) indicates the the PW is in pending state to become active(i.e. up)

eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpXcCctUp.name: eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpXcCctUp
eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpXcCctUp.description: This object indicates the status of the VPN cross connect circuit state. A value of true indicates that the VPN circuit is connected with its remote site and attachment circuit is up (eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpInputCctUp is true). A value of false indicates that the remote site is not presently connected, this mean that either the PSN is not reachable or the attachment circuit is down or signaling parameters mismatched.

eriRouterMplsL2VpnLdpInputCctUp.description: This object indicates the status of the VPN attachment circuit. A value of true indicates that the VPN attachment circuit is up. A value of false indicates the attachment circuit state is down.

eriRouterUdpL2vpnStaticDscpCode.description: Diffserver code for the CES over UDP PW. Default is Zero. The dscp code values are listed as follows: 0..63 Differentiated services codepoint value af11 Assured Forwarding - Class 1/Drop precedence 1 af12 Assured Forwarding - Class 1/Drop precedence 2 af13 Assured Forwarding - Class 1/Drop precedence 3 af21 Assured Forwarding - Class 2/Drop precedence 1 af22 Assured Forwarding - Class 2/Drop precedence 2 af23 Assured Forwarding - Class 2/Drop precedence 3 af31 Assured Forwarding - Class 3/Drop precedence 1 af32 Assured Forwarding - Class 3/Drop precedence 2 af33 Assured Forwarding - Class 3/Drop precedence 3 af41 Assured Forwarding - Class 4/Drop precedence 1 af42 Assured Forwarding - Class 4/Drop precedence 2 af43 Assured Forwarding - Class 4/Drop precedence 3

A value of down(2) indicates that the remote site is not presently connected. A value of standby(3) indicates the the PW is in pending state to become active (i.e. up)
